OL,3,CFares across Transport for Wales up by
OL,4,Can average of 4.6%
OL,6,FThe Cabinet Secretary for Transport,
OL,7,FKen Skates MS said it's a balance
OL,8,Fbetween keeping costs increases low
OL,9,F"whilst ensuring Transport for Wales
OL,10,Fare able to create revenue to meet
OL,11,Ftheir rising costs and reduce subsidy."
OL,13,FHe said: "We understand the any
OL,14,Fincrease in fares is unwelcome for
OL,15,Fpassengers, but we have tried to keep
OL,16,Fthe increase as low as possible.
OL,18,F"It is also important to recognise
OL,19,Fthat increasing majority of passengers
OL,20,Fno longer use these regulated
OL,21,Fproducts."
